00:06:39.064 --> 00:06:41.567
And Kevin [bleep], the owner,
who's still the owner,

00:06:41.600 --> 00:06:42.868
runs over and goes,

00:06:42.901 --> 00:06:45.538
"Sir, we will honor those.

00:06:45.571 --> 00:06:47.106
For the kids."

00:06:47.139 --> 00:06:48.908
So the next thing I see

00:06:48.941 --> 00:06:51.644
is my buddy Moe
with a giant cardboard box

00:06:51.677 --> 00:06:53.112
full of Big Breakfastes.

00:06:53.145 --> 00:06:54.747
I'm like, holy shit, we did it.

00:06:54.780 --> 00:06:56.415
We did it.
Brilliant.

00:06:56.448 --> 00:06:59.385
And then right behind him
is Kevin [bleep],

00:06:59.418 --> 00:07:01.420
the owner of McDonald's
with another big box

00:07:01.453 --> 00:07:03.088
of Big Breakfastes.

00:07:03.121 --> 00:07:07.493
And I realize, I'm gonna
be fired in about five seconds.

00:07:07.526 --> 00:07:08.828
And Kevin [bleep],

00:07:08.861 --> 00:07:11.096
that guy is such a jerk,

00:07:11.129 --> 00:07:12.765
he didn't even
take the food back.

00:07:12.798 --> 00:07:13.999
He just looked at me in the car

00:07:14.032 --> 00:07:15.668
and just gave me that, "I'm...

00:07:15.701 --> 00:07:17.336
"I'm so disappointed.

00:07:17.369 --> 00:07:21.240
"I considered you assistant
manager material, Tom.

00:07:21.273 --> 00:07:23.242
You could've ended up
at Hamburger U."

00:07:23.275 --> 00:07:26.612
Anyway, so that's my last day
at McDonald's.

00:07:26.645 --> 00:07:29.248
So...later in life...

00:07:29.281 --> 00:07:31.584
I know, it's sad.
It was a great job.

00:07:31.617 --> 00:07:33.285
Later in life, I got sober,

00:07:33.318 --> 00:07:35.020
and when you get sober
you have to make a list

00:07:35.053 --> 00:07:36.789
of all the people
you need to make amends to.

00:07:36.822 --> 00:07:38.624
And mine was
a pretty extensive list.

00:07:38.657 --> 00:07:41.527
And...once I got past
the girlfriends

00:07:41.560 --> 00:07:45.030
whose credit I'd ruined,
I got to McDonald's

00:07:45.063 --> 00:07:47.867
and Paul's Discount,
and I sent them checks.

00:07:47.900 --> 00:07:50.369
And...I called Kevin [bleep].

00:07:50.402 --> 00:07:53.639
And he's such a nice guy,
he cried.

00:07:53.672 --> 00:07:55.307
And he wouldn't take the money.

00:07:55.340 --> 00:07:57.810
He had to give it to
the Ronald McDonald House.

00:07:57.843 --> 00:07:59.478
How nice is that, right?

00:07:59.511 --> 00:08:02.047
'Cause I'd stolen, you know,
$10,000 worth of food.

00:08:02.080 --> 00:08:04.016
I mean, that's pretty--
like, that is...

00:08:04.049 --> 00:08:05.985
The one thing I did do,
when I left,

00:08:06.018 --> 00:08:07.953
they stopped putting pockets
on the uniforms.

00:08:07.986 --> 00:08:12.525
'Cause I--you know.
Anyway...

00:08:12.558 --> 00:08:15.227
but there's a happy ending,
because one time

00:08:15.260 --> 00:08:16.829
I hosted "Saturday Night Live."

00:08:16.862 --> 00:08:19.164
And I got to play a McDonald's
manager,

00:08:19.197 --> 00:08:21.000
And this was when Bill Clinton
was president

00:08:21.033 --> 00:08:22.568
and would always go to
McDonald's.

00:08:22.601 --> 00:08:25.671
And the great Phil Hartman,
who I love too...

00:08:25.704 --> 00:08:27.072
Yeah, everybody...

00:08:27.105 --> 00:08:28.741
[cheers and applause]

00:08:28.774 --> 00:08:33.178
Most of the people that I love
are dead now apparently,

00:08:33.211 --> 00:08:36.181
but Phil Hartman was wonderful,
and I had--

00:08:36.214 --> 00:08:38.083
I played Kevin [bleep].

00:08:38.116 --> 00:08:39.685
I had his name tag on there
as a tribute to that guy,

00:08:39.718 --> 00:08:42.021
so that's a happy ending to
that story.

00:08:42.054 --> 00:08:44.890
Thank you guys very much
for being here.

